bilingual.target: 科科是一个著名的品牌。

bilingual.source: Many consumers have high brand loyalty to this brand.
bilingual.target: 许多消费者对这个品牌有很高的品牌忠诚度。

bilingual.source: Their brand loyalty makes them always choose the same brand.
bilingual.target: 他们的品牌忠诚度使他们总是选择同一个品牌。
奇美是一个著名的品牌。
你最喜欢的品牌是什么？

bilingual.source: The chips from this brand are always saltier than others.
bilingual.target: 这个品牌的薯片总是比其他品牌的更咸。
奥迪是一款德国汽车品牌。
这个商城有很多品牌店。
我喜欢这个品牌的巧克力。
古驰是一个著名的奢侈品牌。

list.abstract: Brand，为90后创作型歌手殇小眯2015年最新单曲。

yingyinNormal.en: And they built something else as well, a brand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们还会建造其他的东西，一个品牌。

yingyinNormal.en: Who you are is your brand, and saying that a brand is simply a name is like saying Abraham Lincoln is simply a name, Or Mahatma Gandhi, God.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而你，就是你的品牌，而说你的品牌，只是个名字，就像在说亚伯拉罕·林肯只是个名字，圣雄甘地，上帝只是个名字。

yingyinNormal.en: It looks like "Eat it, eat it, you losers," might just be your brand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看来"吃屎吧，废柴们，"可以当你们的品牌名啊。

yingyinNormal.en: But you have political instincts. And you're a brand. You're St. Alicia.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但你有政治直觉，你有品牌效应，你是圣人艾丽西娅。

yingyinNormal.en: Go after the clients I represent. Correct. You're a brand now. Saint Alicia.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从我代理的客户下手。对，你现在是品牌，圣人艾丽西娅。

yingyinNormal.en: It also turned out that people who bought store brand medication didn't feel as well.
yingyinNormal.zh: 研究还发现购买了普通品牌药物的人，同样也感觉治疗效果不好。

yingyinNormal.en: Good. Another part of your brand is that you stood by your husband. Six years ago.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很好，你品牌的另一组成部分，就是你支持你的丈夫，6年前的事了。

yingyinNormal.en: Darling, I hired these people for their expertise, and ultimately, they feel that we would be doing the brand a disservice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 亲爱的，我雇这些人来给我专业意见，最终，他们觉得我们是在为这个品牌帮倒忙。

yingyinNormal.en: As many of you know, recently Massimo Corteleoni has agreed to finance the expansion of the James Holt label transforming the work of this visionary artist into a global brand, which is really an exciting enterprise.
yingyinNormal.zh: 正如大部分人所知最近马西莫·科特利让内决定为詹姆斯·浩特这个品牌注资，将这位富于创造灵感的艺术家的作品转变成一个全球品牌，一个振奋人心的产业。

yingyinNormal.en: Who are you? I'm Peter Brand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你到底是谁？我叫皮特布兰德。

yingyinNormal.en: I wouldn't leave you behind, Dr. Brand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不会丢下你的，Brand博士。

yingyinNormal.en: You know my father, Professor Brand. We're NASA.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你认识我父亲， Brand教授，我们是NASA的。

yingyinNormal.en: You're a scientist, Brand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是个科学家，Brand。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, Cooper. Professor Brand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好，Cooper Brand教授。

yingyinNormal.en: Today, people, we are gonna debut the brand-new Care Bear bikini!
yingyinNormal.zh: 都听好了，今天就是爱心熊比基尼的处女秀！

yingyinNormal.en: It's new every time. It's brand new every night. It's very, very exciting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 每一次都是新的。每晚都是完全不同的。非常，非常地激动人心。

yingyinNormal.en: And I'll tell you that the one thing they understood about this brand-new nation was to stick together, because every direction they turned was brand-new undiscovered country.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要告诉你们的是对于这个新成立的国家他们认识到最重要的一点就是团结一致，因为他们做的每一个决定都是全新的，前无古人的。

yingyinNormal.en: But her cows produce a lot of waste, and she's found a brand-new way to use it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但她的奶牛就浪费不少了，她找到了一个新方法加以利用。

yingyinNormal.en: He fed them the science and specs. All so they could build him a brand-new body.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他提供人类技术和规格！好让他们为他打造全新躯壳。

yingyinNormal.en: So who wants to go in the back, and see how amazing our brand-new cupcake shop is?
yingyinNormal.zh: 有谁想去后面看看我们新的蛋糕店?

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Offering up such a theory during a time of high tension between scientific and religious minds was <highlight>branded</highlight> as heresy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在科学思想和宗教思想关系高度紧张的时期提出这样的理论被冠以异端邪说之名。

examination_example.sentence: We hail them as Americans in the making, or <highlight>brand</highlight> them as aliens to be kicked out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们要么称赞他们为未来的美国人，要么就给他们冠以需要驱逐的外国人之名。

examination_example.sentence: By offering on-trend items at dirt-cheap prices, Cline argues, these <highlight>brands</highlight> have hijacked fashion cycles, shaking an industry long accustomed to a seasonal pace.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 克莱因指出，通过以极低的价格出售流行服装，这些品牌已经控制了时尚流行周期，动摇了该行业长久以来流行周期随季节而变化的节奏。

examination_example.sentence: Gap year experiences can lessen the blow when it comes to adjusting to college and being thrown into a <highlight>brand</highlight> new environment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 空档年的经历可以减轻适应大学、进入全新环境的冲击。

word_usage.usage: brand作动词时，为及物动词，其后可直接接名词或者代词，如：We have branded our cattle. 我们给牛打上了烙印。

examination_example.sentence: In the year 2004, at the height of over-exposure of the Burberry check, the <highlight>brand</highlight>'s turnover was £715.5 million.

examination_example.sentence: In the same year, a CGI Bruce Lee appeared in a Chinese-language ad for a whisky <highlight>brand</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同年，一个计算机生成图像的李小龙的出现在一个威士忌品牌的中文广告中。

examination_example.sentence: In a survey of 54 of the world's leading <highlight>brands</highlight>, almost all of them reported that consumers are showing increasing care about sustainable lifestyles.

examination_example.sentence: But now Chinese <highlight>brands</highlight> have won the hearts of people at home and abroad.

examination_example.sentence: In the future, Chinese <highlight>brands</highlight> will continue to develop.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 未来，中国品牌将继续发展。

examination_example.sentence: Coca-Cola, for example, placed the letters of its famous <highlight>brand</highlight> further away from each other to show social distancing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，可口可乐将其著名品牌的字母彼此放置得更远，以显示社交距离。

examination_example.sentence: However, it takes even more energy and water to go through the recycling process than to make a <highlight>brand</highlight> new paper bag.
